Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.35,sign_0_1_Nobody_can_swim_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,No one can swim in the same river water twice
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.87,0:00:04.35,italics,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,"No one can swim in the \Nsame river water twice."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:09.53,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,That's an old saying Hiro told me about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:15.24,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,Everything changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.03,0:00:18.66,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,all things eventually pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.19,0:00:20.98,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,and nothing remains stagnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.09,0:00:23.51,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, like a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.24,0:00:27.32,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,That is the nature of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.13,0:00:35.30,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I often recall these words and \Nthe fact that no one can halt the flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.04,0:00:38.10,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,in this world without Papa,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.65,0:00:42.35,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,where we don't need to \Npilot the FRANXX anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.85,0:00:45.69,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Say, "Aah."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:48.16,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:50.31,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Open your mouth, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:00:56.61,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.05,0:02:35.17,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we increase the portions a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:39.38,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,No can do. We only have food \Nreserves for around one more year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:42.47,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,But the veggies are growing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.47,0:02:46.20,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. We'll be able to harvest \Nthem in a couple of months.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.20,0:02:47.10,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Kokoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:50.74,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,We're so lucky that Kokoro \Nknows so much about plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:54.52,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I don't really know \Nanything about harvesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:55.81,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.81,0:02:59.40,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,So we should maintain the status quo until \Nwe have a firm estimate for the harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:00.77,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Tch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.77,0:03:02.99,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuru, how's the energy system looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:06.75,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,We still haven't serviced the unit \Nthat's been acting up lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.75,0:03:08.50,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,Output's gone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:12.46,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Futoshi, how'd the water \Npurification system look?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:14.84,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Its efficiency has dropped, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:17.70,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:23.18,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Should we really keep using magma energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.56,0:03:26.77,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,It originally belonged \Nto the klaxosaurs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.77,0:03:28.93,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what else can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.93,0:03:30.98,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,How else are we gonna live?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:34.48,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,It's used in food preservation and \Nfor treating wounds too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:35.77,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.54,0:03:39.98,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I need to lie down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:41.32,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.32,0:03:42.61,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:50.96,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel, Hiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.06,0:03:55.08,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,About magma energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:56.63,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:05.90,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we've got to survive any way we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.90,0:04:08.89,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Let's figure out what we need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:11.14,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:13.21,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.21,0:04:16.61,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's impossible right now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.29,0:04:19.65,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Given the state Zero Two is in...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.15,0:04:25.61,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,I've said this before, but please let \Nus know if we can help in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.87,0:04:28.44,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We're all worried about you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.73,0:04:31.53,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Ichigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:35.29,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Don't apologize, dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.29,0:04:38.75,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Code 015. We have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:42.93,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.93,0:04:46.05,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,You've been refusing to eat since yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:52.60,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,Eating that stuff can only abate \Nour condition for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.27,0:04:55.72,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,What we really need is maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:04:59.94,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave your food here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:09.87,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.68,0:05:12.75,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,I understand where you're coming from,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:17.30,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,but I cannot make any decisions \Nwithout Papa's approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.30,0:05:22.00,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,But if this keeps up, we're all\Ngoing to die eventually!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.82,0:05:24.01,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:34.97,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:41.54,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,If the farm works out and we \Nwon't have to worry about food,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:43.53,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,we can start planning for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.81,0:05:49.09,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,I went and spoke to the new Nana.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:52.77,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,I asked for power and purification \Nsystem repairs, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.77,0:05:54.68,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,No go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:56.37,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:05:59.83,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Life in the outside world is hard, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.39,0:06:02.65,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You run into obstacles everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.43,0:06:04.36,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,This is like...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.36,0:06:07.22,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,"No one can swim in the \Nsame river water twice."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.49,0:06:10.84,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,It's a saying Hiro taught me in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.57,0:06:13.72,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,I recall it often these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.23,0:06:21.59,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hopefully, Hiro and Zero Two\Nwill get better soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.13,0:06:22.95,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.87,0:06:28.21,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Even more cuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.05,0:06:31.19,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:39.79,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:41.49,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.49,0:06:44.12,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the concern, but I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.12,0:06:45.48,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,My fever's gone down, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.10,0:06:47.23,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.23,0:06:49.25,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.07,0:06:53.22,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, you look like a wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:55.41,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Sit this one out, Hiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:06:56.55,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.05,0:06:58.93,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hiro, you-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.20,0:07:01.89,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? An earthquake?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.03,0:07:03.96,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:12.63,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a klaxosaur?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:16.84,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's a VIRM soldier, too!\NThey killed each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.74,0:07:19.61,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.61,0:07:20.93,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.93,0:07:22.46,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:25.88,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Are they gonna attack Earth again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:27.80,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.45,0:07:31.72,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,The klaxosaurs are flying off again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.69,0:07:34.93,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:36.69,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Kokoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:38.65,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.65,0:07:39.76,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Let Nana know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.05,0:07:41.10,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kokoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:40.61,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.61,0:07:41.63,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.10,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:45.38,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,The results are in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:49.37,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,Her urine sample revealed traces \Nof human chorionic gonadotropin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.37,0:07:51.53,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,According to the database,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.53,0:07:55.03,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,this is a hormone secreted during pregnancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.18,0:08:01.78,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,"Pregnancy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:03.73,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:13.64,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,It is considered impossible for a \Npregnant woman to pilot the FRANXX.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.64,0:08:15.51,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,Past records indicate abortion,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:20.27,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,or removal of the fetus, \Nas one of the treatments used.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:23.46,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me know when\Nyou've decided what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.33,0:08:26.02,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:27.78,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.50,0:08:29.65,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,What should I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:31.78,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.78,0:08:32.68,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Kokoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.68,0:08:35.03,main,556,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me! Tell me what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.29,0:08:35.03,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Boys, please give us a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.57,0:08:43.46,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.84,0:08:47.31,main,326,0000,0000,0000,,Hiro, what am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.31,0:08:48.19,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuru, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.19,0:08:49.38,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.45,0:08:53.73,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.03,0:08:58.94,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,What are we supposed to do? \NWhat's the right thing to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.94,0:09:00.71,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:07.73,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.07,0:09:09.11,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:11.16,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Zero Two?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.22,0:09:14.49,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:19.03,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:25.46,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two, have you regained...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:37.34,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.69,0:09:39.51,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:45.02,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on. You've gotta be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.02,0:09:47.39,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,They were growing fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:52.23,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We gave them water and fertilizer \Njust like the instructions said, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.43,0:09:58.41,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:07.00,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:09.83,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Nana?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.77,0:10:15.42,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.83,0:10:17.17,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.17,0:10:19.21,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.21,0:10:20.93,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just following the doctor's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.53,0:10:24.61,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:27.94,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,A database of adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:33.44,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,All of the memories stored in their \Nbrains have been copied and archived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.58,0:10:38.66,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,"Cast your bodies aside, and take \Nyour minds to eternal paradise"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.06,0:10:44.66,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you just leave me be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.01,0:10:48.82,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,I don't serve a purpose anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:51.71,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,You should've just abandoned me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:10:58.84,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.66,0:11:06.18,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:13.44,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.49,0:11:16.07,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:20.69,flashback,7,0000,0000,0000,,Why are the children who were deemed unfit \Nand disappeared from Garden here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.17,0:11:24.66,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,After the siege of Gran Crevasse,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:26.73,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,I received an email from the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.43,0:11:30.50,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it was programmed to be \Nsent automatically after his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.50,0:11:37.06,sign_16556_20_Take_Nana_to_the,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Take Nana to the location below
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.11,0:11:33.93,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from location data, it also \Ncontained a message from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.45,0:11:37.64,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,It said to bring you here, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.06,0:11:42.38,sign_16689_24_You_two_become_t,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,You two become the children's new adults
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.17,0:11:41.69,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,"You two become the children's new adults."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.92,0:11:45.24,main,7,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:46.44,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Nana!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.01,0:11:49.77,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad you're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.95,0:11:52.39,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Help...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.39,0:11:53.56,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.30,0:11:58.78,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,This is just conjecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.22,0:12:02.50,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,but decades of extracting magma energy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:06.99,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,may have depleted the soil itself of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.48,0:12:11.00,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:13.42,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Like, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:19.05,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,So even the planet itself has rejected us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:23.83,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.83,0:12:24.93,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.59,0:12:49.80,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,How's Ichigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.51,0:12:52.83,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,They say it was overwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.15,0:12:57.27,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,She's such a fool, worrying about\Neveryone but herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.83,0:13:00.36,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,She's really such a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.57,0:13:06.64,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:07.96,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Goro?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.96,0:13:11.68,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You heard about the field, right?\NI really want to figure something out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.00,0:13:15.44,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,If we all work together, we can \Nsurely make it productive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:17.17,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.37,0:13:19.46,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:23.23,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.23,0:13:24.00,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.00,0:13:24.78,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:36.71,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,You'll catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.71,0:13:38.52,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back inside, Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.52,0:13:39.25,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:41.50,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me, Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.69,0:13:54.27,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you'll be okay by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:56.48,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I want to keep watch over her myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.46,0:13:58.37,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.25,0:14:05.69,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.42,0:14:06.99,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.82,0:14:27.76,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:29.94,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't she finish it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.98,0:14:36.02,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,"And so, she turned into a bird
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.34,0:14:38.95,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,and took to the skies,\Nleaving the prince all alone."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.09,0:14:44.47,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,You knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.56,0:14:49.54,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that we'd have \Nto part like them someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.71,0:14:53.03,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,So you left the last page to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.77,0:14:55.27,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:58.05,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,That's just cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.33,0:15:24.53,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.48,0:15:27.69,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.07,0:15:29.86,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Are you up there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.19,0:15:31.99,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:34.42,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Zoom in on that part!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:38.37,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Mistilteinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.06,0:15:39.99,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.47,0:15:45.78,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that Mistilteinn contains soil \Nfrom before this planet became a desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:49.94,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,Then if we start making fields\Nthere and gradually expand them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.94,0:15:51.29,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:55.22,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go let everyone know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.18,0:16:03.65,main,8,0000,0000,0000,,Code 016.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.35,0:16:05.61,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:07.83,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He said we stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.83,0:16:09.28,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.03,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head to Mistilteinn already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:13.15,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Hiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.01,0:16:15.28,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Hiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.16,0:16:19.62,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I need to talk to you about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.01,0:16:21.87,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:24.00,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to space?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:25.69,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,To meet Zero Two?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:29.21,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about? \NZero Two's in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.81,0:16:33.95,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Her mind is in Strelizia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:37.01,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,And she's fighting in space even as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.34,0:16:41.15,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on. My brain can't keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.15,0:16:44.15,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,How are you gonna get to space, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.15,0:16:45.27,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,There's a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.59,0:16:48.07,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,A way the klaxosaurs left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.08,0:16:52.77,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,I found it while looking for cultivable land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.93,0:16:56.77,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,It's a klaxosaur ship, \Nbut for some strange reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:16:59.32,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,I could access its internal systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:07.32,flashbackitalics,8,0000,0000,0000,,Decide whether you want \Nto fight or accept your ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:10.74,flashback,16,0000,0000,0000,,I can take this ship to space?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.74,0:17:11.81,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:14.41,flashback,8,0000,0000,0000,,But this course...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:19.30,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Mars orbit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.09,0:17:22.34,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that stupidly far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.34,0:17:23.21,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.21,0:17:26.13,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,W-Will you be able to come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.13,0:17:27.19,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.19,0:17:29.29,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be up against those monsters, y'know!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.29,0:17:30.61,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:33.30,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,We're saying that you could lose your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:34.07,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:37.16,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.65,0:17:42.65,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,But if I don't act now, I'll never\Nbe able to forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:44.62,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.05,0:17:47.29,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to let you guys know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.72,0:17:48.70,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:50.09,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:55.30,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.37,0:17:58.49,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.05,0:18:03.89,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,We need to work together \Nagain and start from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:06.27,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you have to do this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:10.98,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave Zero Two alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:13.14,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,We made a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.14,0:18:15.01,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we were torn apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:17.53,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,we'd go to get the other, no matter how far.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.20,0:18:20.89,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Zero Two kept up her end of the promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:24.99,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,So I can't just sit here and do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.42,0:18:27.12,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.37,0:18:30.53,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad about letting you all down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:33.75,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,But I want you to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.50,0:18:38.02,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, you feel bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:41.33,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, you want us to understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:49.81,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Have {\i1}you{\i0} ever spared a thought for \Nhow the people close to you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:53.66,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.66,0:18:57.94,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You run off, make your own decisions, \Nand never stop to think about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:00.90,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Papa and the adults are gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.90,0:19:04.33,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,but forget freedom, we've got our \Nhands tied on every single thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.33,0:19:08.08,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Have you stopped to think about how \Nworried we are about all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:10.08,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,When someone collapses, \Nall we can do is watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.45,0:19:13.96,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,And yet we're trying our \Ndamned hardest to live on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:16.64,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,But here you are, running off to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:18.84,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,What are we supposed to \Nunderstand about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:23.72,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,There are people doing all they can to \Nsupport you because they want you to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:25.87,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,And you're trampling their \Nfeelings as you leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:28.93,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you want us \Nto understand about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:35.29,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.19,0:19:42.44,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,If Zero Two won't smile for me,\NI might as well be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:50.33,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Goro! Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:06.09,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we'll ever \Nfind something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.83,0:20:12.27,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Something that means the world to us, \Nthat we'd choose over anything else, like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.09,0:20:17.53,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,That differs from person to person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.31,0:20:22.78,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Goro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.29,0:20:25.51,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.29,0:20:30.04,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,That was never about how everyone felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:32.04,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,It was all about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:36.29,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one scared of the \Nworld that I chose myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.87,0:20:37.71,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,That's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.72,0:20:40.55,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.89,0:20:48.14,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:50.14,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:53.59,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,No one can swim in the \Nsame river water twice,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.03,0:20:59.15,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,so all we can do is find \Nour own true path in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:04.36,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We'll keep looking for it until we find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.26,0:21:09.01,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Our lives have only just begun, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.29,0:22:04.01,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.01,0:22:05.83,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.44,0:22:11.10,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you guys going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.01,0:22:16.56,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We're taking you to Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:21.06,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,But we're not just doing \Nit for you, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:25.38,main,666,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't kick those guys' asses, \Nno farm can help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.38,0:22:28.36,main,214,0000,0000,0000,,And letting them kill us or waiting \Nhere to die isn't our style.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.36,0:22:32.17,main,390,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. Our lives have only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.17,0:22:33.83,main,196,0000,0000,0000,,There you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.31,0:22:36.49,main,7,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of things while we're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.49,0:22:37.24,main,N7,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.24,0:22:39.29,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,Let us join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.69,0:22:40.99,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,Nines.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.99,0:22:43.50,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.50,0:22:48.88,main,9a,0000,0000,0000,,We were created to fight, so we \Njust want to fulfill our purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.88,0:22:51.76,main,9b,0000,0000,0000,,And outer space doesn't sound \Ntoo bad as a resting place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.32,0:22:55.72,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We don't plan on dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.72,0:22:58.19,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come back, make more fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.19,0:22:59.97,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,and live on, come what may...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.22,0:23:03.27,main,15,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how pathetic it may make us look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.68,0:23:09.54,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Hiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.36,0:23:17.69,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You've made your decision. \NI won't fight it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.21,0:23:19.65,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're even.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.24,0:23:24.66,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,This is the path we've \Nchosen in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.33,0:23:27.14,main,56,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get to fight it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.46,0:23:30.23,main,16,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.50,0:23:34.05,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,Everything changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.98,0:23:38.79,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,all things eventually pass,\Nand nothing remains stagnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.52,0:23:41.37,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, like a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.31,0:23:47.57,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,But if that nature of our world scares you \Nout of appreciating what you have now,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.94,0:23:50.18,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,you'll never grasp any kind \Nof future for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.10,0:23:55.67,italics,56,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we reached out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.08,0:24:00.50,sign_33134_360_Episode_1,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 22
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.08,0:24:00.50,sign_33134_361_Alone_and_Loneso,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Stargazers

